So people of all races who’s travel history you do not know carry the same risk of transmission to you due to the fact prior to this people of various races could have been in China. This is why Chinese race IS NOT EQUIVOCAL to increased risk on its own

It may seem logical at first to say Chinese people are from China therefore they carry greater risk. This is a logical error. Without knowing when someone was last in China you cannot attribute increased risk to them. You would have to know travel history.

The disease originated in China (geographic origin). The disease is new so we cannot say that there is an increased risk related to one race without long term studies. The risk would be based on RECENT TRAVEL not country of ORIGIN.
